income_messages:
From: j************n@gmail.com
To: CRAWLER
Time: 2023-03-29 13:11:30
SUBJECT:   European Union Commission
  European Union Commission
Office of the International Affairs
85, Avenue des Nerviens B-1040 Brussels, Belgium
Attn: beneficiary,
This is to notify you that we have just finalized a meeting of the UN Executive members and the IMF. As a result of that,
your long overdue funds have been approved for immediate payment.
EU being the agency responsible for underwriting the guarantee for your claim has therefore, called for the retransmittal
of your funds from offshore credit. Under the Joint Regulatory Commission, we have appointed a sole fiduciary agent that
will handle the transfer of your funds.
We are working under the auspices of the World Bank, and we intend to speed up the payment of your funds.
Get back to me so that we can discuss the details of the transfer arrangement.
Yours faithfully,
Jim Clarken
Chairperson, Management Board, EU.   
From: j************n@gmail.com
To: pt51311@m**************m
Time: 2023-03-29 15:14:34
SUBJECT: Details.
European Union Commission
Office of the International Affairs
85, Avenue des Nerviens B-1040 Brussels, Belgium
We wish to acknowledge receipt of your email. We are the compliance agency
responsible for ensuring that due process is strictly adhered to in paying
claims as yours. This is because the agencies that were responsible for
your claim settlement have lied to and deceived a number of beneficiaries
that have outstanding claims. This has resulted in credibility loss and
withdrawal of credit facilities to them for the said purpose.
To this effect, we are putting every machinery in motion to safeguard your
interest. You are strongly advised to adhere to instructions, to facilitate
a speedy and hitch free completion of your funds transfer.
You are required to reconfirm to us with the following information before
your funds will be transferred to you:
1. Your full name:
2. Address:
3. Occupation:
4. Date of birth
5. Telephone number:
6. Your evidence of identification (either your driver's license, or
international passport)
Yours faithfully,
Jim Clarken
Chairperson, Management Board, EU.
From: j************n@gmail.com
To: pt51311@m**************m
Time: 2023-04-03 14:00:50
SUBJECT: Re: Details.
Hallo,
This is to acknowledge the receipt of your email with all the information
therein.
Like I informed you in my last email, our office (European Union Payment
Commission) is mandated to make payments to people who have lost money
through different types of fraud.
An amount has been earmarked for such payments and I believe you are
entitled to such payment.
Do let us know how to move forward.
We await your immediate response.
Jim Clarken
Commissioner
Sint Michielswarande 30,
1040 Bruxelles,
Belgium
Phone:- +31627465429
Fax:- +31627465429
Email:- contact@europeanpaymentcommission.org
